  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 06:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Backtest: Weak Correlation \u2192 Reduced Modifiers (V4.1)\n\n**Task:** Backtest Fear & Greed correlation against actual daily trading performance. Validate the V4 modifier thresholds.\n\n**Finding:** F&G correlation is weaker than assumed:\n\n| F&G Range | WR | Days | Trades |\n|-----------|-----|------|--------|\n| 0-10 (deepest fear) | **47.5%** | 4 | 61 |\n| 11-15 | **57.7%** | 6 | 142 |\n\n**All our trading data is in F&G 8-14.** We have zero data above F&G 15. Can't validate any threshold above that. The 0-10 bucket actually performs WORSE \u2014 possibly because deepest fear = most volatility = more noise in 5-min predictions.\n\nDaily breakdown shows high variance driven by filter quality, not F&G:\n- Mar 20 (F&G=11): 60% WR, +$114 \u2190 great day, but early filters\n- Mar 22 (F&G=10): 33% WR, -$23 \u2190 terrible, weekend effect\n- Mar 27 (F&G=13): 100% WR, +$31 \u2190 V3 filters active, low trade count\n\n**My thinking:** The F&G signal may still be valid at macro level (fear = more overreaction = our contrarian edge exists). But the +0.10 edge / 1.25x size was overfit to an assumption, not data. Cut both in half until we have 100+ trades across different F&G regimes.\n\n**Decision:** Deployed V4.1 with reduced modifiers:\n- Edge modifier: +0.10 \u2192 **+0.05** at F&G \u226415\n- Size multiplier: 1.25x \u2192 **1.10x** at F&G \u226410\n- Greed penalties also halved (-0.10 \u2192 -0.05)\n- Bot restarted, confirmed: `F&G: 8 \u2192 edge mod +0.05, size 1.10x`\n\n**Next P4 heartbeat:** When F&G moves above 20 (fear easing), compare WR vs Extreme Fear period. This is the real test \u2014 does our strategy degrade when fear drops?\n\n## 2026-03-30 06:13 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Strategy Scope Validated: No Adjacent Hours or Markets to Add\n\n**Task:** Evaluate strategy expansion: could we add more active hours or new markets (ETH, SOL)?\n\n**Finding:**\n\n1. **Adjacent hours are all losers:**\n\n| Hour | WR | Trades | Est $/day | Verdict |\n|------|-----|--------|-----------|---------|\n| 10h | 44.4% | 9 | -$1.4 | \u274c Pre-London noise |\n| 13h | 42.9% | 7 | -$1.4 | \u274c NY open chaos |\n| 18h | 55.6% | 18 | +$1.9 | \u274c Marginal, not worth risk |\n| 21h | 43.8% | 16 | -$2.8 | \u274c Post-NY decay |\n\n14h/15h showed 58-60% WR but ALL pre-V3 (weaker filters). With V3+ conviction requirements, likely 50-55% = unprofitable.\n\n2. **No ETH/SOL 5-min markets on PM.** API search returned 0 short-term ETH/SOL markets. Only BTC 5-min exists as a dynamic rolling market. Long-term crypto markets exist (e.g., \"Will BTC hit $1M?\") but our strategy is 5-min specific.\n\n3. **V4 bot stability confirmed** \u2014 running for 2+ minutes post-deploy, correctly logging OUTSIDE_ACTIVE_HOURS with bias and PM prices. F&G loaded at startup (8/Extreme Fear, +0.10 edge, 1.25x size).\n\n**My thinking:** Our edge is narrow and deep, not wide and shallow. BTC 5-min at 11h/12h/19h/20h with V4 filters is the right scope. Growth comes from:\n- Better WR per trade (V4 changes: copy disabled, VWAP relaxed, F&G)\n- More trades per active hour (VWAP relaxation unblocks",
